OOC: I will assume that Nightshift is running away from the jungle
rather than deeper in since deeper in means little to no traction with
the rougher road.

&lt;BACK IN CHARACTER&gt;

As NIGHTSHIFT skillfully manuvers through the more open landscape,
using his superior ground speed against the larger and definitely
better armored SLAG and SLUDGE, he finds that he is more or less
successful. Moving in and around trees and across open terrain he is
able to draw them further and further away.

SLAG is able to muster up a good bit of ground speed even over the
roughest of landscapes, but he is more ponderous that the quicker
moving SUV. And SLUDGE, is well SLUDGE. Large and powerful but not
nessesarilly fast moving in beast mode.

&quot;Me sludge think vehicle is too fast!&quot; SLUDGE said as he ran as
swiftly as he could after NIGHTSHIFT.

&quot;Well slow him down!&quot; SLAG said as he ran.

SLUDGE stopped and thought for a moment and then began to stomp his
feet on the ground sending ground quakes at NIGHTSHIFT causing small
fissures to open up NIGHTSHIFT, most of them 6 feet long and three or
four feet deep each!

At the same time SLAG stopped and just opened his mouth sending 3000
degrees Celcius flames at the hopefully floundering or atleast
distracted SUV!

